All natural all dewy 💗

Makeup & hairstyling : @varshak_makeupartist & team 

In frame @khushbooakarnia ❤️

There goes several steps in getting flawless base read below 👇🏻

1. Prepping your skin with a good suitable moisturiser is extremely important, irrespective of your skin type. (Cleanse, hydrate and moisturiser)
2. Understand skin concerns you’re going to deal with & act accordingly. ( dry skin patches, oily T zone , acne etc)
3. Colour correction- for discoloured skin/ pigmentation which will not get covered with a concealer alone. Use very less colour correctors, don’t cake up at once. 
4. Foundation & Concealing - use little product at once and build up only when required. Remove excess with a beauty blender but don’t overdo it, this can create patchy base.
5. Wait for few minutes or fan your base before applying any kind of loose powder so it gets settle. 

If you’re doing all of the above steps and your base looks flawless but a little heavy, don’t worry & let is settle. It all blends together if each of all above step is done right. Enjoy 💕

Mature skin makeup ✨

Mature skin makeup focuses on enhancing natural beauty while addressing common concerns like fine lines, texture, and dryness. Key tips for makeup on mature skin include:

Hydration: Start with a moisturizing primer or serum to create a smooth base.
Light Coverage: Opt for a lightweight foundation or BB cream that provides even coverage without settling into fine lines.
Cream Formulas: Choose cream blushes and eyeshadows for a dewy, youthful finish.
Avoid Heavy Powders: Instead of powders, use a light touch of translucent setting powder only where necessary to avoid a cakey look.
Luminous Highlighter: A subtle highlighter can add a healthy glow without emphasizing texture.
Neutral Tones: Soft, neutral shades for eyes and lips help create a balanced, elegant look.
These techniques help bring out your natural beauty while providing comfort and confidence throughout the day.
